Well, when I was Acting Peregrin, the rule was a divided field of equal (or
geometrically consistant) parts color and metal, for ex Checquies,
gyronies, etc, Per ___, Tierced per ___ were treated as a fur, and thus any
non-component color, tincture, or the opposing metal may be used atop
provided the charge crosses the borders. Mind you, that was AS24-25 era...
Otherwise, No color on color, no metal on metal, no color on a fur or vair
of which said color is a component, no metal on a fur or vair of which said
metal is a component. Tinctures (Purpure, Sanguine, Sky and Tenne) treated
as colors.

Since the field was chequy of 9 Gu and Ar, a non Gu, non ar item could be
placed  on it. Key point: A non-specified charge is assumed to be 1/3 of
the height and width, so in that blazon, according to what I was taught by
Mistress Flanna of Dunwalton and Her Excellency Ariana Silkenfire, chequy
of 9 WOULD need the "Overall" to guarantee the crossing of the boundaries
of the center Gu square of the chequy.

In service to the dream, I remain,
