draw it out, and make certain it follows the basic rules... the Heradrese
can be overwhelming. My Pendragon players hate me, since I make them
attempt a blazon in heraldrese from the trick (the miniature drawing)...
then I correct the heraldrese, and have a DIFFERENT player trick it (draw
it) from the blazon. Then again, I also keep a Roll of Arms for my PD
games... Then again, they beg me to run more.

More ob Trav: If imperial heraldry exists, verbal distinction between Poni
and Pony would probably be made in Imperial Heraldrese... And for those
using language rules, Heraldrese should probably be a separate (In GT, M/A,
M/E if you know the base language) language, but defaulting to the higher
of (Root Language 2+ serves as Heraldrese 1) or (Heraldry -1). It took me
almost a year to learn to blazon, and I always have had to have the
dictionary  of heraldry handy.

