    'body' => 'Glenn Goffin writes:
<snipt>(I\'ve forgotten his noble status, if
>any; is there an official UPP for Santanocheev?).

I haven\'t found any, but I\'ll take a stab at what his Soc
might be. Santanochev is regular IN; so he either enlists
and goes through OCS or he goes through the Naval
Academy. The enlist/OCS route implies to me that allot
of work ethic would be involved; not something that I
would think Santanocheev would be into. OTOH, getting
a commission through the Naval Academy looks good on
the resume. A pc needs SOC 8 to even try to get into
the Academy. His promotions from \'Rear Admiral\' to Sector
Admiral over two years would indicate to me at least 2
tours as a Naval Attach (+1 SOC, and promotion). Assuming
no other additions to SOC, the absolute minimum SOC for
Santanocheev would be 10.

Of course its hard to get into the Academy on SOC 8. In
addition, Santanocheev is going out of his way to move up
in the 3I, so figure at least an extra +1 SOC from moving
with his \'political and social connections\'. That\'s SOC A to
start, with +2 SOC (N Attach) and +1 SOC from
Command Duty(probably from a Shore Duty tour).
My guestimate: SOC D

>> From: Glenn Goffin <gmgoffin@yahoo.com>
>> >Dan Roseberry <rosebee@troi.csw.net>
> >>Who were Santanocheev\'s "political and social
> >>connections"? the persons who had promoted him to
