> >so the Matriarch (who also holds the Imperial title
> >Duchess of Mora) wields a lot of power in the sector.
>Alan Bradley<alanb@elf.brisnet.org.au>
>I\'ve always assumed some kind of tie to the Tukera clan.  But Delphine
is
>good, too.

An explanation for why the Oberlindes ship Bloodwell got destroyed?
Tukera\'s annoyance with Oberlindes causes them to complain to
Santanocheev to due something. Santanocheev goes overboard...
BOOM no more Bloodwell.

Some other items...
Back to the \'political and social connections\' bit. From 1103 to
1107 (maybe even earlier than that) we have lots of political
and economic unrest  in the Regina subsector. Adv1 implies that
allot of this unrest comes from 3I nobles and bureaucracy.
Naturally, there were a few other problems (Efate\'s civil war,
Ine Givar, Zhodani influence, etc etc) but I\'m trying to
understand what the role of 3I nobles/bureaucracy had in
causing problems in the Regina area. My impression was
that Santanocheev and allies were causing most of the
problems. If Santanocheev had less of a role in those events,
then who was causing the problems? Was Norris facing
opposition from nobles and bureaucrats in his own subsector?

From the SOC discussion above, it seems probable that
Santanocheev served a couple times as a Naval Attach.
This led me to a wild thought:  what if Santanocheev had
served as an Attache at the 3I embassy on Chronor? The
Zho\'s co-opt, turn, or otherwise gain control over the man
to use as an agent. If the Imperial Ambassador managed to
catch wind of the plot, the Zhodani would, of course, have
to silence her. Hmm...did\'nt a ambassador get killed there?

Another thought:  how about Santanocheev\'s home world
being Porozlo? It would fit the slavic name. Also, being
from their might cause Santanocheev to think that the Zhos
would never be able to fight their way into the Rhylanor
triad because "our forces are so much more powerful than
they were during the 3FW". This attitude is actually echoed
by others in various TNS bulletins concerning the ability of
SW forces reaching Rhylanor. "So let the Zho\'s run to my
home world. They\'ll be cut to pieces by our new ships and
I\'ll break the sieges at Efate and Jewel."--Santanocheev

Finally, there is the inevitable Lucan/Santanocheev concept.
I didn\'t want to do this; it seemed a little to tidy and cheesy.
But I suppose one could connect the two. And for GT:Trav
people, Lucan and Santanocheev\'s son might create some
mischief. Not my IMTU; YMMV.

