    'date' => 'Thu, 30 Dec 1999 17:23:45  0700',
    'body' => 'Fellow TMLers:

Just back from a well deserved rest and catching up on the traffic.
Here are some of my takes on the tramp traders and truckers subject

There is no such thing as a "tramp trucker."  Being the son of
a trucker, there are:  long haul, short haul, double bottomed, 
triple bottomed, straight jobs and gypsies.  All of these are called
rigs in some form or fashion.  Also note that this is US trucker slang.
I don\'t know what a Canadian trucker or an Australian would call these.

long haul:  cross country,  extra fuel tanks slung under the rig with
    living arrangements attached

short haul:  limited to local or city routes, definitely not interstate

double bottomed:  dragging two trailers

triple bottomed:  dragging three trailers

straight job:  standard truck or lorry

gypsies:  truckers that "live" out of their rig and "own" their own rig

mixed rig:  a straight job dragging a trailer

rig:  the truck or lorry that actually drags the trailer

IMTU:  All my free traders that are not subsidized by the government
or other entity are called, yep, you got it, "gypsies."

Have a safe New Year.

367 days left in this millenium.

Eric
