Designer\'s notes:

I freely admit that this is a hideous example of conspicuous
consumption.  After all, even AuricTech Shipyard\'s ELECTRA II-class
yacht is only 1000 dtons, and costs merely MCr 1,166.19.  I mainly
designed this ship (as I\'m sure is quite obvious) as a play on the "Y2K"
term.  Few individual sophonts would ever spend the 2.5+ gigacredits to
purchase such a craft; OTOH, this yacht may be considered suitable for
heads of state and/or CEOs of Imperial megacorporations.  Some fleets
may wish to purchase the JUBILEE-class as C3 ships, or VIP transports,
hence the fiber-optic computers (with flight-computer backups) and
overall redundancy of power plant, commo gear, and sensors.

I kept the ship at TL-12, so that M:0 campaigns could use it. ("As
_if_!")  I figure that, with the exception of laser systems, few
potential owners would need the ship upgraded to a higher TL.  Potential
owners who prefer a higher-tech version of this ship may contact
AuricTech Shipyards at wombat@premier.net .

