JUBILEE-class yacht from prying enemy eyes.

Note that there are 64 Large staterooms, and 20 Small staterooms, for
only 70 sophonts normally carried.  While the customer can, of course,
order the ships with any custom combination of staterooms that will fit
in this space, the default configuration is as follows:

35 Large staterooms for crewbeings (each crewmember gets a Large
stateroom; the captain gets a two-stateroom suite [includes office
space]).  After all, the crewmembers quite possibly _live_ aboard this
ship, for six months or more at a time.

29 Large staterooms for the yacht\'s owner, and any guests, divided into
suites as follows:

Owner\'s suite (4 Large staterooms);
10 Guest suites (2 Large staterooms each);
5 Regular staterooms (1 Large stateroom each, for lesser guests).

20 Small staterooms for lackeys.

Most ship\'s facilities (emergency low berths, galleys, etc.) are
designed around each stateroom having single occupancy (assuming that
each stateroom in a suite has an occupant).  In other words, although
the ship\'s listed expected occupancy is 70 sophonts, the JUBILEE-class
yacht has sufficient food, emergency low berths, and other facilities to
support 84 human-sized beings without any hint of overcrowding.  Food
carried is sufficient to support 84 humans for up to 22 weeks, without
resort to emergency rations.

This yacht is definitely high-performance for TL-12 (J-3, 3 Gs
acceleration, 3 Gs compensated).

