    'month' => '12',
    'index' => 'ej505',
    'body' => 'I have envisioned a TL12+ fresher that is activated by a code when you
enter, unique to the individual of course. It then analyzes all the matter
"deposited" and decides what is wrong with you (if anything), if you are
getting "large" or "small" and makes adjustments automagically in the food
dispenser to negate whatever effects you are showing. You can eat all you
want or as little as you want and the food will be adjusted accordingly to
not/contain things such as fat, vitamins, minerals, hormones, calories, etc.

I also see electrical stimulus to keep a person fit and strong while they
sleep or rest. This could be incorporated into your bunk or there could be a
station on the ship where you go and climb into a pod or something similar
to receive this "exercise". We already have something like this today for
paralization victims (if you can afford it) and it seems to work a little
bit from what I\'ve read. By TL12 it should work fine.

Both of these operations could be running as part of the life support
functions on the ship\'s computer. I haven\'t developed this too far yet but I
do like it and am using it in a short story I\'m working on for BITS. More to
come later.

This is my answer as to why all the characters look like "Greek Gods". There
can even be settings for those cultures that like their specimens a little
larger/smaller (whatever is a pleasing appearance to them; i.e. the movie
Hawaii and the Queen of the Hawaiian people) without making them unhealthy.

Thom Harris

