    'body' => 'Eris wrote:
> There\'s underpowered and then there\'s *really* underpowered.  <g> I
> rate power requirements at three levels when I design ships.  First,
> there\'s the power requirement with *every* system at full power,
> ships sometimes carry a reactor this powerful.  Second, is the power
> requirement will all systems that would be running similtaniously
> (don\'t need power maneuver in jump space or jump drive/grid in
> normal space, CG/AG doesn\'t have to run at full power at all times,
> etc.), every ship should *exceed* this number. 

IMTU, you need to run the FTL drive for a while (about 1 High Guard
combat round) before you actually leave normal space. If you\'re 
trying to jump out of a combat situation, it\'s nice to have power
for both the normal space drive and the FTL drive so you don\'t 
become a newtonian target drone (and shortly thereafter, dead)
in the meantime.

