In my Traveller universe, organized crime exists at many levels
and in many permutations, so just about any answers could be
true.  Often, criminal organizations are composed of members of
an extended family, and it may be necessary to marry into the
family.  Standards for skill levels and whatever are usually not
terribly important.  As long as you\'re good people, you can be
employed by the family or organization.  If you prove yourself,
you can marry in and get a bigger piece of the action and of the
power.  

Although criminal organizations frequently specialize (e.g.,
assassins don\'t usually get involved in racketeering or drug
distribution, but may be hired by them; grifters and swindlers
don\'t usually get involved in violent crimes), most of them
usually have use for a foul-tempered, unscrupulous bully.

- --Glenn
