Ok, so it\'s not really the 3rd millennium for another year; however, =
here\'s what we at THUDDD have planned for the year 2000.  Of course, by =
the time you read this it will be probably be the year 2000.

Okay, enough confusion about the new millennium.  :-)

While we are waiting on Black ICE to get the Commerce Raider together, =
we will go ahead and do the Modular Cutter for THUDDD 11.  THUDDD 12 =
will be the Commerce Raider and THUDDD 13 will be skipped.  I am still =
looking for an Assistant Coordinator for THUDDD 14.

Confused?  So am I.  I really shouldn\'t write this stuff after starting =
the New Years Eve celebration (hey, at least this time, I didn\'t spell =
it with an \'s\').

Okay, here\'s the spec\'s for THUDDD 11 (the official release date for =
this is 1/3/00, but what the heck):

[From IN Press Release 0035-109-1009, Capital/Core]
      Lord Jonas Mac Finny, a representative of the Imperial Bureau of =
Transportation (IBoT), announced an IBoT initiative to upgrade current =
standards for small cargo transport, specifically a new standard for =
what is commonly referred to as a Modular Cutter. IBoT was prompted to =
announce this initiative by the constant complaints concerning the =
massive cost of current standard units.
      Lord Mac Finny provided spec\'s for the current standard units:
               Modular Cutter
            Tons 50
            Crew 2=20
            Cargo 15
            7 Size Rating
            0 Fire Control Rating=20
           Volume 700
            Passengers High/Medium 12
            Passengers Low 0
            Controls: Civilian Standard
            0 Jump Rating
            4 G Rating/Maneuver Drive
            4 Power Plant Rating
            13.5 Rating/Scoop/Refine
            0A 2P 0J Sensor Rating
            0 Armor  Cost: 28 MCr
             =20
            TL 9=20



            6 Structure=20
          =20

               Modular Cutter: Using a 50-ton hull, the cutter is =
capable of 4G, carries 2 tons of fuel, and has a crew of two. It has 30 =
tons committed to special detachable modules; the craft has 2.t tons =
excess space available for weaponry or ancillary items.=20

            Three interchangeable modules are routinely available for =
the modular cutter:
                  The ATV Module (which includes an operational ATV) is =
30 tons. It can land and retrieve an ATV on a world surface. The module =
can serve as an ATV storage location, if desired.
                  The fuel module, with 30 tons of fuel tankage, serves =
as a fuel skimming vehicle and storage tank.
                  The open module is a customizable frame with 30 tons =
of excess space, which can be allocated to passenger couches, fuel, =
cargo, cabin, or staterooms.
             =20

    =20
      Indicating that the new standard should meet or exceed the current =
standard for less money. Preferably much less. Lord Mac Finny was quick =
to assure this reporter that the winning design firm would be given a =
contract to produce an initial run of 2 dozen Modular Cutter and would =
be able to expect annual contracts to produce hundreds more after the =
completion of trials.

Due to concerns expressed by some, this competition will be closed to =
those who only design using GURPS.  We wouldn\'t want any of the THUDDD =
designs to influence anything produced for use in an actual Traveller =
source book, now would we?  ;-)

All kidding aside, we wish the developers of the Modular Cutter Source =
Book all the best in the world.

I\'m looking forward to seeing those Non GURPS designs.
- --
Jason
